### [Proverbs Chapter 24](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#001.md)

[Proverbs 24:2](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#002.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_002">pro 24:2</span></span>

Destruction - How they may oppress and destroy others.

[Proverbs 24:3](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#003.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_003">pro 24:3</span></span>

Through wisdom - There is no need that thou shouldest raise thy family
by ruining others, which thou mayest more effectually do by wisdom.

[Proverbs 24:4](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#004.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_004">pro 24:4</span></span>

By knowledge - Which in scripture phrase includes the love and practice
of what we know.

[Proverbs 24:5](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#005.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_005">pro 24:5</span></span>

Is strong - Is courageous and resolute, and able by wisdom to do greater
things than others can accomplish by strength.

[Proverbs 24:6](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#006.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_006">pro 24:6</span></span>

Thy war - War is better managed by wisdom than by strength.

[Proverbs 24:7](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#007.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_007">pro 24:7</span></span>

A fool - For a wicked man, whose sins enfeeble his mind, and make it
incapable of wisdom. Openeth not - He knows not how to speak acceptably,
and profitably in the publick assembly.

[Proverbs 24:8](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#008.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_008">pro 24:8</span></span>

Shall be called - Though he cover his wicked devices with fair
pretences, he shall be branded with that infamy which is due to him.

[Proverbs 24:9](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#009.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_009">pro 24:9</span></span>

The thought - The very inward thought or contrivance of evil, is a sin
in God's sight.

[Proverbs 24:11](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#011.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_011">pro 24:11</span></span>

Deliver - When it is in thy power. Drawn - By the violence of lawless
men.

[Proverbs 24:12](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#012.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_012">pro 24:12</span></span>

Consider - That this is only a frivolous excuse.

[Proverbs 24:13](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#013.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_013">pro 24:13</span></span>

Eat - This is not a command, but a concession, and is only here
expressed to illustrate the following verse. Honey in those parts was an
usual food.

[Proverbs 24:14](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#014.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_014">pro 24:14</span></span>

A reward - It is not only sweet for the present, but brings a sure and
everlasting reward.

[Proverbs 24:16](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#016.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_016">pro 24:16</span></span>

Falleth - Into calamities, of which he evidently speaks both in the
foregoing verse, and in the following branch of this verse. Fall -
Frequently into irrecoverable destruction.

[Proverbs 24:17](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#017.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_017">pro 24:17</span></span>

Falleth - Into mischief.

[Proverbs 24:18](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#018.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_018">pro 24:18</span></span>

From him - Understand, upon thee, which is implied in the Hebrew phrase.

[Proverbs 24:20](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#020.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_020">pro 24:20</span></span>

No reward - All his happiness shall quickly and eternally perish. The
candle - All their comfort and glory shall cease.

[Proverbs 24:21](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#021.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_021">pro 24:21</span></span>

To change - That are unstable in their obedience to God or to the king.

[Proverbs 24:22](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#022.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_022">pro 24:22</span></span>

Who knoweth - Who can conceive how sore and sudden will be the ruin of
them that fear not God, and the king.

[Proverbs 24:23](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#023.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_023">pro 24:23</span></span>

These - The counsels following, to the end of the chapter, no less than
those hitherto mentioned, are worthy of their consideration.

[Proverbs 24:25](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#025.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_025">pro 24:25</span></span>

Rebuke - That publickly and judicially rebuke and condemn the wicked.
Delight - The peace of a good conscience.

[Proverbs 24:26](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#026.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_026">pro 24:26</span></span>

Shall kiss - Shall respect him. A right answer - That speaks pertinently
and plainly, and truly.

[Proverbs 24:32](../../../bib/kjv/pro024.htm#032.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_032">pro 24:32</span></span>

Received - I learned wisdom by his folly.

